      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tnetworks, backhaul (i.e. the links to the core network) or metro networks should be entirely\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\toptical in order to optimise the energy efficiency of the entire network.<br> Reference\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- <a href=\"http://home.deib.polimi.it/pattavina/pub_archive/conf-TIWDC13a.pdf\">Source</a>\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"flip\" id=\"flip_3_2\">Optical transmission - installing optical bypassing in\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tcore networks, using fibre in wired access networks <span class=\"checkmark\" name=\"3_2\"></span>\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"panel\" id=\"panel_3_2\">In such a configuration, traffic not intended for the\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tIP node remains in the optical layer and does not pass through the IT router. The capacity\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tof the router is reduced and the associated power consumption as well. Furthermore energy\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tlosses related to optical / electronic / optical conversions are also reduced.</div>\n");
      out.write("\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"flip\" id=\"flip_3_2_1\">Replacing existing devices by new more-energy-efficient<span\n");
